<br>
I set up a bank of hotkeys with 8 different /book # keys.<br>
/book 1     /book 7<br>
/book 13   /book 19<br>
/book 25   /book 31<br>
/book 37   /book 43<br>
<br>
With these hotkeys, every page in my book is within 1 hotkey and one page flip away, except for 47-50, but I only have old junk spells that deep anyway.<br>
<br>
Now, every hotkey leads to a section with a different series of spells, with the major ones on those two pages and the minor ones one page flip away.  Main spells on pages 1 and 2, common buffs on 7 and 8, other mezes and stuns on 13 and 14, etc, etc, etc.<br>
<br>
I still have a few empty spaces throughout my book, so whenever I get a new drop I can place it where I need it without moving around a whole bunch of other stuff.<br>
<br>
Every type of spell of grouped on the same pages with the other spells of the same series (fears, roots, nukes, dots, stuns, mezes, illusions, enchants, manas, dispells, etc.) and in order of spell level.  This makes finding any spell so much easier for me than when I would move older spells deeper and deeper in my book when I reached a new spell level. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/ushetraranyhyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shetra Ranyhyn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#330000>(4/23/02 6:05:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfaqs.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=46.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Spellbook</span><hr size=1> I laid out my spellbook as follows :<br>
<br>
/book 1-2: Current Buffs<br>
<br>
/book 3-4:  Travel (gate, bind, invis, see invis, enduring and alliance)<br>
<br>
/book 5-6:  Illusions<br>
<br>
<br>
/book 7-8: combat<br>
<br>
/book 9-10: stun/crowd control<br>
<br>
/book 11-12:  all enchant spells (ie silver, clay...)<br>
<br>
/book 13 -14:  pets<br>
<br>
/book 15-16:  Mis ( I put things like sentinel, bind and serpent sight..things I rarely use)<br>
<br>
/book 17 +:  I put my old spells in which i have bette upgrades.<br>
